overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking validation against the Statement of Work and a detailed
  specification. The agent meticulously analyzed the existing codebase,
  identifying several critical gaps in functionality. Subsequently, the agent
  systematically implemented these missing features. This included adding a 1-10
  severity scale for tiredness with crucial safety warnings, integrating
  detection and tailored recommendations for complex sleep disorders like COMISA
  and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and enhancing the Excessive Daytime
  Sleepiness (EDS) scoring with a weighted system. Furthermore, the CSV export
  functionality was significantly expanded to capture all questionnaire data,
  and new sections were introduced to screen for pain, chronic fatigue symptoms,
  and to collect medical and mental health history. The implementation involved
  extensive modifications across data types, validation schemas, UI components,
  and both web and PDF report generation logic, ensuring the application now
  aligns more closely with the comprehensive requirements.
